extends pagewrapper

block content
    #main
        .header
            h1 Hearts of Iron 4 Division Calculator
            h2 a tool for planning you army buildup
        .content
            h2.content-subhead How to use this Calculator:
            p
                | To use this calculator, just use a provided template or design your division from the scratch in the division designer below. You can also choose a template and edit it in the designer. Afterwards, enter some data about your production efficiency, factory efficiency and the time span of this calculation. Now you can specify if you either provide a number of divisions you want to equip in the time span and get the number of factories you need to do so, or you can provide the number of factories that you have and the calculator will tell you how to assign this factories in the best way and how many divisions you can produce with it. Finally hit the "Calculate!" Button and enjoy your result.
                p
                | If you provide the calculator a number of factories and let it assign them by itself, it can happen that one factory get assigned to less or to much. This happens due to a rounding problem. This problem occurs specially if you assign a very low number of factories to a complex template.
            h2.content-subhead Now let's enter your data:
            form.pure-form.pure-form-aligned
                fieldset
                    .pure-control-group
                        label(for='template') You can select a template
                        select#template(onchange="setTemplate()")
                            option(value='empty') Empty
                            option(value='20i') 20 Width Infantry
                            option(value='40i') 40 Width Infantry
                            option(value='40iat') 40 Width Infantry With Anti Tank
                            option(value='20t') 20 Width Tanks
                            option(value='40t') 40 Width Tanks
                            option(value='spacemarines') Space Marines

            |You can edit the table by clicking on the cells - use it like the division designer in the game.
